etts that manufactures products for the wine industry its first product the coravin system uses patented technology to pour wine without taking the cork out of the bottle contents  history  timeline  product details  reception  awards  references historyedit coravin inc was founded in  by greg lambrecht a massachusetts institute of technology graduate and medical device inventor nick lazaris the former ceo of keurig joined as ceo on july   coravin launched its first product the coravin  system in september  coravin announced the opening of their european headquarters coravin bv located in amsterdam frederic levy former nespresso executive was appointed ceo in february  by june  coravin inc announced that it had secured  million in series c financing timelineedit history of coravin timeline december  greg lambrecht first has idea to pour wine without removing the cork june   first successful wine pour by prototype december  filing of first provisional patent application august   first patent issued february  coravin llc formed september  blind taste test with master of wine sandy block legal sea foods january  blind taste test with sommelier jeff porter bb hospitality april  nick lazaris joins coravin llc as presidentceo july   coravin launches its first product – the coravin  wine access system december  coravin llc becomes coravin inc july  coravin announces a retail partnership with harrods its first international business partner september  coravin announces the opening of its eu headquarters in amsterdam december  coravin launches with distribution partner watson’s wines in hong kong february  fred levy former president of nestle nespresso usa is appointed ceo of coravin inc may  landry’s announced that it would be rolling out a coravin wine by the glass program in all  morton’s the steakhouse restaurant locations across the us june  coravin inc wins silver stevie in american business awards’ “startup of the year” category product detailsedit the coravin system uses a medical grade needle and a capsule of argon gas to pour a bottle of wine through the cork the cork is never removed this helps prevent oxidation increasing the longevity of the wine it accomplishes this by first inserting a hollow needle through the cork the user then presses a trigger to pressurize the bottle with argon gas when the user releases the trigger the wine pours into the glass the needle is removed from the cork a naturally elastic and porous material which then reseals protecting the wine from oxidation and leaving the remaining wine unaffected receptionedit when it launched in july  the coravin system garnered attention from both media and wine professionals described by some as “transformational” and a “game changer” due to the potential to change wine consumption habits jancis robinson financial times nothing i know of preserves wine in an opened or accessed bottle for years as this system does joe bastianich restaurateur wine expert and coravin investor “this product is nothing short of amazing for both restaurateurs and wine lovers alike jennifer jolly usa today “wine lovers rejoice the ridiculously cool coravin system can provide a glass of wine from a bottle without ever actually popping the cork preserving the freshness of the vessel with zero hassle” alder yarrow founder and editor of vinography “i’ve never written a product review on vinography because i’ve never met a wine accessory that was worth writing about but there’s a first time for everything apparently” cooks illustrated “the results were indisputable tasters found the wines we poured from coravin which had been open for a month just as good as wine from freshly opened bottles” gear patrol “the coravin wine system  is to wine what the black hat is to the white rabbit a magician’s portal without removing the cork which would aerate the wine and disrupt the rest of the bottle it takes the wine inside the bottle and allows you to pour it outside the bottle how it works is relevant and interesting on the level that all small engineering marvels are interesting but the big reveal is the fact that it actually does work” by june   complaints had been made of broken bottles following use of the coravin coravins founder estimates that only  in  bottles will break and he attributes the issue to bottles that have been previously dropped and cracked in response to the complaints coravin sent purchasers a neoprene protective sock to cover the bottles awardsedit the coravin system has been nominated and won several awards for recognition in innovation or technology november  – popular science “best of what’s new” in the home category december  – la revue du vin de france “the most innovative product in the world of wine” for  may  the drinks business magazine “best product launch” april  edison awards – gold in the “consumer products” category june  the american business awards – silver stevie award in “startup of the year” category july  international design excellence awards – finalist in “kitchen accessories” category referencesedit referencesedit  about coravin coravin january   accessed august   httpwwwcoravincomcompany  zimmerman ed ive seen the needle no damage done how greg lambrecht is changing the wine world the wall street journal  december  accessed on august    coravin inc opens european headquarters in amsterdam coravin  stop opening start tasting  sept  web  july   coravin inc appoints frédéric levy as chief executive officercoravin  stop opening start tasting  feb  web  july   coravin inc raises  million in series c funding coravin  stop opening start tasting  june  web  july   the inspiration coravin accessed august   wwwcoravincominspiration  millar rupert coravin launched in hk the drinks business  dec  web  july   coravin partners with landrys inc to expand bytheglass offerings to wineloving patrons nationwide coravin  stop opening start tasting  may  web  july   coravin wine access system named finalist in  american business awards coravin  stop opening start tasting  may  web  july   asimov eric the coravin makes great wines more accessible by the glass the new york times september   accessed august   httpwwwnytimescomdiningthecoravinmakesgreatwinesmoreaccessiblebytheglasshtmlr  robinson jancis coravin drinking without pulling the cork financial times october   accessed august   httpwwwftcomcmssceaefeabdehtmlaxzzalfbu  coravin launches transformational wine access system business wire july   accessed august    jolly jennifer tech now innovative gadget gifts usa today december   accessed august   httpwwwusatodaycomstorytechinnovativetechgifts  yarrow alder coravin and the future of winebytheglass vinographycom a wine blog september   accessed august   httpwwwvinographycomarchivescoravinandthefutureofwinehtml  akeny matthew wine preservation’s silver bullet gear patrol  oct  web  july   summers nick september   coravin greg lambrechts corker of a wine idea businessweek retrieved december     best of whats new  home popular science november   accessed august   httpwwwpopscicombownproductcoravinwineaccesssystem  linnovation de lannée coravin  january  la revue du vin de france retrieved june   from httpwwwlarvfcomvinsinventiondelanneecoravinetatsunisgreglambrechtasp  eads lauren db awards  the winners revealed the drinks business june   accessed august   httpwwwthedrinksbusinesscomdbawardsthewinnersrevealed retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitlecoravinoldid categories wine companieswine accessoriescompanies established in hidden categories orphaned articles from october all orphaned articles navigation menu personal tools not logged intalkcontributionscreate accountlog in namespaces article talk variants views read edit view history more search navigation main pagecontentsfeatured contentcurrent eventsrandom articledonate to wikipediawikipedia store interaction helpabout wikipediacommunity portalrecent changescontact page tools what links hererelated changesupload filespecial pagesper