er vp  general manager of coravin europe francois silvain vp it mike rider vp engineering yvethe tyszka vp of marketing michelle mcfaul vp of events  community affairs angus scott senior director of operations kareem ghobrial north america sales director executive bios greg lambrecht founder  board member greg lambrecht is the inventor founder and board member of coravin™ mr lambrecht is also founder and executive director of intrinsic therapeutics inc a venturebacked medical device company focused on addressing the needs of patients with spinal disorders in addition mr lambrecht is the founder and board member of viacor inc a startup medical device company in the boston area previously greg was vice president of product development  marketing at stryker a global orthopedic implant company where he directed the development and launch of numerous successful orthopedic implants mr lambrecht also held various management positions within pfizer’s medical technology group where he directed and implemented a breakthrough process for inventing and developing new technologies mr lambrecht holds a masters of science in mechanical engineering and a bachelor of science in nuclear engineering from the massachusetts institute of technology he holds numerous patents in the fields of gynecology general surgery cardiology and orthopedics executive bios josh makower cofounder  board member josh makower md is a cofounder and board member of coravin™ having worked closely with greg lambrecht for more than  years coravin presented a natural opportunity for dr makower to join mr lambrecht in bringing coravin to market he is the founder  chief executive officer of exploramed development llc serves as a consulting professor of medicine at stanford university medical school and is cofounder of stanford’s biodesign innovation program dr makower has founded six medical device companies through the exploramed incubator and holds more than  patents in the fields of cardiology ent general surgery drug delivery orthopedics and urology dr makower holds an mba from columbia university an md from the nyu school of medicine and a sb degree in mechanical engineering from the massachusetts institute of technology lastly dr makower serves as a venture partner for nea and is chairman of exploramed neotract and moximed and on the board of directors for intrinsic therapeutics and ceterix executive bios frédéric levy ceo  board member frédéric levy joined coravin after spending nearly  years with nestlé’s nespresso group in his most recent role as president of nespresso usa he established key wholesale relationships with major retailers including williamssonoma sur la table bloomingdale’s and macy’s he also helped define nespresso’s strategic branding and positioning in the united states including the development of its firstever us media campaign in  and the launch of the inaugural nespresso boutique bar retail locations previously frédéric directed the international ecommerce development for nespresso in europe australia and asia where he developed launched and oversaw management of nespressocom executive bios jerome chevalier board member jerome chevalier runs quadrille capital an investment firm based in paris france which led the last round of financing in coravin prior to its launch in europe quadrille capital invests globally in technology companies and funds worldwide and has done previously two investments with greg lambrecht and josh makower the two founders of coravin jerome has executed over  private equity transactions with quadrille capital and previously with quilvest a european family office with bn under management he worked before at lazard originating and executing transactions in the fields of technology internet healthcare and energy jerome serves on the boards of coravin and of chateau hautbailly a pessac leognan grand cru classé he is a graduate of essec ecole supérieure des sciences economiques et commerciales in paris executive bios rob beck chief financial officer rob beck cpa is the chief financial officer at coravin inc with a strong background in financial planning and analysis rob is an experienced leader in global corporate finance he leads all financial activities and relationships of the company on a global basis including internal accounting and administrative functions he began his career as an auditor at arthur andersen and held various roles in financial management at keane inc before joining coravin rob served as the vp  cfo of the home robots division hrd at irobot for three years and most recently as the svp of corporate finance also at the irobot corporation he is a graduate of merrimack college executive bios sanam thakur managing director asia pacific sanam thakur is coravin’s managing director for asia pacific her area of oversight includes hong kong singapore china japan australia new zealand india and south east asia previously sanam was director of category marketing for dfs group where she led conceptualization business strategy and financial plan team structure and development for a new business unit for dfs she also was responsible for  marketing campaigns for brand partners including cartier tiffany hermes and estee lauder past work also includes merchandising at dfs as well as international projects and marketing for women’s specialty clothing retailer bebe stores inc sanam holds a degree in international development from university of california berkeley with a concentration in east asia she is permanently based in hong kong executive bios maarten dekker vice president and the general manager of coravin europe maarten dekker is vice president and the general manager of coravin europe responsible for developing and leading a high performing team responsible for ecommerce field sales marketing communications operations and accounting maarten began his professional career in  within the krasnapolsky hotel group in amsterdam before joining nestlé netherlands in  where he spent more than ten years in various management positions in business development and sales prior his current role at coravin maarten held the position of vice president bb north america at nespresso usa inc where he was responsible for the creation development and implementation of the nespresso bb strategy for north america maarten holds degrees in financial economic management and marketing management from the hotel school in maastricht the netherlands executive bios michelle mcfaul vice president of events  community affairs michelle mcfaul is the vice president of events  community affairs at coravin inc  before to joining coravin michelle served as vice president of special events and community affairs at nespresso usa where she was responsible for the unprecedented growth and development of their “tasting is believing” marketing strategy prior to nespresso usa she held the title vice president of public relations at the loews corporation as principal at her own firm michelle o mcfaul public relations she managed an impressive client list including preston robert tisch swissair mca music and the principality of monaco michelle holds a bs from the rochester institute of technology executive bios michelle stacy board member michelle stacy is a senior leader with the consistent ability to run and scale businesses currently on the board of directors of irobot corp flex pharma inc and young innovations inc in addition to coravin inc she is also a director advisor to the cambridge group the expert in resident at the harvard innovation lab and is a professional speaker on leadership innovation and women’s leadership in her previous position michelle served the president of keurig inc a  billion division of keurig green mountain nasdaq gmcr prior to joining keurig michelle had a successful year career with gillette including the procter  gamble acquisition of gillette in  michelle received her masters in management from j l kellogg graduate school of management at northwestern university and her bs from dartmouth college executive bios francois silvain vp it francois silvain is the vice president of information technology at coravin inc before to joining coravin francois served as vice president of product management at pointillist where he defined and led the development of a disruptive analytic application to conduct fast and real time customer behavior analysis that would require otherwise data scientists longer lead time and complex data warehouse francois is also the coinventor of a new paradigm to conduct customer journey and behavior analysis before francois was vice president of technology at sap lab in charge of sap precision marketing a real time mobile marketing platform enabling marketing organizations to inform and influence consumers in realtime at the point of decision with one to one and personalized marketing interactions francois brings  years of experience in the software industry especially in crm marketing and mobile he founded successfully  startups and was cto  vp product in  others executive bios mike rider vp engineering  operations mike rider is vp of engineering and operations at coravin™ hes a product development executive with  years of leadership in new product development manufacturing and operations serving global markets previously mike served as vp of business development at for irobots home business division he has also held various product development leadership roles at polaroid mike is a graduate of the university of lowell and holds an mba from worcester polytechnic institute executive bios yvethe tyszka vp of marketing yvethe tyszka is the vice president of marketing at coravin prior to joining coravin yvethe served as a director of marketing at jarden consumer solutionsnewell brands where she successfully launched omnichannel campaigns driven by consumer insights to garner awareness engagement and advocacy while also supporting sales and profitability growth targets in addition to her deep unders